704933f-b.title: Brooklyn: Hicks Street - Grace Court
704933f-b.text:
Hicks Street, at the S. W. corner of Grace Court,
showing the Grace Protestant Episcopal Church, built on
the site of the Jans Remsen House, which was erected
about 1710 and moved to 25 Joralemon Street by William
S. Packer. The churrh was erected in 1848 at s cost of
42,000 8ollars. Richard Upjohn was the architect.
View 1: 1922
View 2: 1928
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
